Charlie Stayt missed out the letter 'c' when he scrawled the word 'education' on a whiteboard at a primary school in Southampton . 
  Viewers took to Twitter to complain about the gaffe . 
  He was broadcasting from Highfield Primary School in Hampshire . 
  Fellow presenter Bill Turnbull made him spell the word out live on air . 
  Stayt later described the error as 'one of those things'